CREATING YELPDEMO SITE
----------------------


1	Adding Bootstrap

	> copy and paste css and javascrip to the header part of the layouts/application file

	>> Styling table

		>> open: restaurants/index file, add:

			> add: <table class="table table-hover table-condensed">

2	Adding Navigation Bar

	> Add navbar to layouts/application file


3	Simplify The Codes

	>> 2 reasons to simplify the codes:

		1. Minimize the typo mistakes, easier to debug
		2. Simple codes, more readable

	>> Use Partials template to simplify the codes

		Note:

		Partial file start with _(underscore)

	>> Create partial file :
	
		layouts/_navbar.html.erb, 
		layouts/_footer.html.erb, and
		layouts/_bootstap.html.erb, 

		> move navigation, footer, and SDN Bootstrap to it
		> render them in the application file.

4 	Build Beautiful Forms		

	1	Styling the form (_form.html.erb)

		> Add class: "form-group: to each div tag
		> Add class: "form-control" to each field
		> Add class: "btn btn-primary" to the submit button

		NOTE: no comma (,) on the submit input

	2	Styling the anker tags on edit page (edit.heml.erb)
	
		> Add class: "btn btn-link" to anker tags	

	3 	Styling the anker tags (show, edit, and destroy) on index page

		> Add class: "btn btn-link" to show, edit, and destroy tags
		> Add class: "btn btn-link" to the input New Restaurant

	4	Styling the link tags Show Page (show.html.erb)
	
		> Add class: "btn btn-link"	to link tags

	5	Styling the link tag on the new.html.erb
	
		> class: "btn btn-link"

	6	Adding Container Fluid to the layouts/application file
	
		> 	<%= render 'layouts/navbar' %>
			<div class="container-fluid">
				<%= yield %>
			</div>
			<%= render 'layouts/footer' %>

				














